<br>
What Poe did was contradict himself....most likely because he's gotta do some serious buttkissing at VI to hold the party line that everything in wizardland is ok. who can blame him actually...if he voices dissent, he's done there....he'll be relegated to a &quot;nothing&quot; position. <br>
<br>
His contradiction lies in the proposition he makes that damage\power wise Wizards are okay(read fixed or not broken), YET he claims to see some reason to increase <br>
&quot;group utility&quot; for wizards with this current line of spells. <br>
<br>
Really the contradiction exist because in saying that Wizards need a group enhancement it BEGS THE QUESTION as to WHY they need such an enhancement?  Shouldn't the &quot;Masters of Direct Damage&quot; and &quot;Arcane Transportation&quot; be a &quot;given&quot; in every group if, as Poe contends, &quot;damage wise&quot; the class does not have a problem? <br>
<br>
Notice he did not answer the question as to why Wizards are not group desirable. He couldn't answer that because to do so, would contradict his statement that all was well with Wizzies on the damage front. <br>
<br>
Bad Organizations can put good people in bad positions. Poe may be trying to make some legitimate headway for us, HOWEVER, and the point of this post, is that we need to look at exactly how far from the forefront of discussion the damage question is. IT's A MILLION MILES AWAY people. Wake up and smell the roses on that singular fact. <br>
<br>
A quick message to Graffe on this:  It's good that you've engaged this person in a dialogue regarding our class, but please know that Mr. Poe is outclassed here when it comes to moving the real obstacles to wizard improvement at VI. Maybe you know this Graffe.....it's possible you've been able to get a take on where exactly Poe sits in this organization????<br>
<br>
I'm going to just close it here.....reminding everyone that the point here is that QUESTIONS that need to be asked aren't even on the agenda to be discussed at VI. There is a lack of honesty and integrity which coats that organization and which possibly good people like Poe get sludged up with at times. <br>
<br>
Goanad<br>
